5:
S-so this is Voluntas Academy... 
It's huge!
14:
Is that permitted? None of us are
affiliated with this academy.
17:
They're doing an open campus
today, so it's fine. I heard about it
from the Guild. They even have a
trial lesson!
26:
Oh? That's interesting. I don't think
I've ever seen you nervous before.
31:
O-of course I get nervous!
Everybody does! Now hurry up, we're
going to be late for class!
34:
So depending on one's senses and
elemental projection, the properties
of the elements are rather
malleable...
37:
Intriguing. This world seems to share
much with my world's teachings
regarding the arcane arts.
41:
Uh... Is that so? It's all gibberish to
me.
44:
Now then, I'd like to ask one of our
visitors to give it a try.
46:
Let's see... You there, young lady!
Would you mind coming up here?
54:
Oh dear... I've never seen her so
nervous.
69:
Hmm... Does this seem less...
controlled than usual?
94:
Piamo! Light, quick, we have to
follow her!
97: That girl... Just what was that?
100:
I'm sorry... I wasn't able to control my
magic.
103:
Don't sweat it. Everybody has days
like that. You were probably just
nervous.
108:
No. If I was a normal student,
studying at a proper school learning
proper magic, this wouldn't have
happened!
111:
But because I'm self-taught, I... I'll
never be good enough...
116:
Your magic sure was something
else! What a surprise!
118:
Are you an adventurer? You must
be, right?! Your magic felt built for
combat! So when are you starting
school?
130:
Oh no, that's the school golem!
Is it going haywire?
133:
Come on, Piamo! This is your
chance to show them your magic is
just as good as theirs!
136:
Students should head inside! Leave
the rest to us instructors!
137: Now... what fool woke up the golem?!
150:
Yes! Alk, I need you to finish it off! 
I'll cast a blessing on you!
164:
You're the girl from the trial lesson,
correct? Could I have a word with
you?
169:
Ah, that's right! You start school
today, don't you?
173: Huh? What are you going on about?
177:
Voluntas Academy is having her
attend special classes as a student
AND a combat instructor.
181: That so? Well, look at you, Teach!
